      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and knead",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Combine the {{strong-white-flour}}, {{fine-sea-salt}}, {{caster-sugar}}, {{instant-yeast}}, {{mixed-spice}}, {{ground-cinnamon}}, and {{cocoa-powder}} in a large bowl. Add the warm {{whole-milk}} and {{free-range-eggs}}. Mix to a rough dough, then knead for 5 minutes. Add the {{unsalted-butter}} a little at a time, kneading it in fully before adding more. Continue kneading for a further 5 to 8 minutes until the dough is smooth and elastic. Knead in the {{dark-chocolate-chips}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bulk ferment, 1.5 hours",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape into a ball, place in an oiled bowl, and cover. Leave at room temperature for 1.5 hours until almost doubled.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shape and proof, 1 hour",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Divide the dough into 12 equal pieces (about 90 g each). Shape each piece into a tight ball by folding the sides under and rolling on the work surface. Place close together on a greased baking tray in a 3×4 grid. Cover and leave for 1 hour until puffed and the buns are touching.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pipe the cross",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Mix the {{plain-flour}} with enough water to make a thick, pipeable paste (about 5 to 6 tablespoons). Transfer to a piping bag or a small ziplock bag with a corner snipped. Pipe a cross over each bun.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 18 to 20 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 18 to 20 minutes until risen and the base sounds hollow when tapped. While still warm, brush with the {{golden-syrup}} for a sticky glaze. Leave on the tray for 5 minutes before pulling apart.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
